Detailed Description

RNDIS command handler functions. This handles RNDIS commands according to the Microsoft RNDIS specification, creating a USB Ethernet network adapter.

static bool ProcessNDISQuery ( uint32_t  OId,
void *  QueryData,
uint16_t  QuerySize,
void *  ResponseData,
uint16_t *  ResponseSize 
) [static]

Processes RNDIS query commands, retrieving information from the adapter and reporting it back to the host. The requested parameter is given as an OID value.

Parameters:
[in] OId OId value of the parameter being queried
[in] QueryData Pointer to any extra query data being sent by the host to the device inside the RNDIS message buffer
[in] QuerySize Size in bytes of the extra query data being sent by the host
[out] ResponseData Pointer to the start of the query response inside the RNDIS message buffer
[out] ResponseSize Pointer to the size in bytes of the response data being sent to the host
Returns:
Boolean true if the query was handled, false otherwise
static bool ProcessNDISSet ( uint32_t  OId,
void *  SetData,
uint16_t  SetSize 
) [static]

Processes RNDIS set commands, setting adapter parameters to values given by the host. The requested parameter is given as an OID value.

Parameters:
[in] OId OId value of the parameter being set
[in] SetData Pointer to the parameter value in the RNDIS message buffer
[in] SetSize Size in bytes of the parameter value being sent by the host
Returns:
Boolean true if the set was handled, false otherwise
void ProcessRNDISControlMessage ( void   ) 

Processes the RNDIS message received by the host and stored in the RNDISMessageBuffer global buffer. If a response is created, the ResponseReady global is updated so that the response is written back to the host upon request.

char PROGMEM AdapterVendorDescription[] = "LUFA RNDIS Adapter" [static]

Vendor description of the adapter. This is overridden by the INF file required to install the appropriate RNDIS drivers for the device, but may still be used by the OS in some circumstances.

uint32_t CurrPacketFilter = 0

Current Ethernet packet filter mask. This is non-zero when the adapter is initialized, or zero when disabled.

uint8_t CurrRNDISState = RNDIS_Uninitialized

Current RNDIS adapter state, a value from the RNDIS_States_t enum.

RNDIS_Message_Header_t* MessageHeader = (RNDIS_Message_Header_t*)&RNDISMessageBuffer

Pointer to the RNDIS message header at the top of the RNDIS message buffer, for convenience.

bool ResponseReady = false

Indicates if a RNDIS message response is ready to be sent back to the host.

uint8_t RNDISMessageBuffer[sizeof(AdapterSupportedOIDList)+sizeof(RNDIS_Query_Complete_t)]

Buffer for RNDIS messages (as distinct from Ethernet frames sent through the adapter. This must be big enough to hold the entire Supported OID list, plus the response header. The buffer is half-duplex, and is written to as it is read to save on SRAM - for this reason, care must be taken when constructing RNDIS responses that unread data is not overwritten when writing in responses.
